casebody.data:
No. 10-9712. David S. Frederick, Petitioner v. Alfonso J. Graham. 563 U.S. 984, 131 S. Ct. 2462,

179 L. Ed. 2d 1206,

2011 U.S. LEXIS 3549. May 16, 2011.

Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis denied, and the petition for writ of certiorari to the Supreme Court of Wisconsin dismissed. See Rule 39.8. As petitioner has repeatedly abused this Court’s process, the Clerk is directed not to accept any further petitions in noncriminal matters from petitioner unless the docketing fee required by Rule 38(a) is paid and the petition is submitted in compliance with Rule 33.1. See Martin v. District of Columbia Court of Appeals, 506 U.S. 1, 113 S. Ct. 397, 121 L. Ed. 2d 305 (1992) (per curiam).
